Product InsightIQ Engine (PIE)
1. Purpose of This Document
This document defines the frontend (FE) / visualization layer for PIE.
The FE layer exists to provide:
Human-readable insight exploration
Transparent evidence and reasoning inspection
Workflow-aligned review and handoff visibility
This document does not prescribe a specific UI framework; it defines canonical screens, components, interactions, and data needs.
2. FE Design Principles
Explainability FirstEvery insight must show “why” (evidence + reasoning), not just “what.”
Progressive DisclosureSummaries first, drill-down on demand.
Governance AwarenessApproval status and governance outcomes must be visible.
Replay & History VisibilityVersion history is a first-class view.
Operational SafetyFE surfaces do not execute actions; they only reveal and route.
3. Primary User Personas
Operator / Strategist — reviews ranked insights and selects candidates for governance review
Analyst — inspects evidence quality, model outputs, and counter-signals
Governance Reviewer — reviews the package that would be approved in GGP
4. Canonical Screens (MVP)
4.1 Insight Feed (Ranked List)
Goal: Rapid triage of the current insight universe.
Core Elements:
Ranking list with:Opportunity StatementConfidence ScoreRisk BandRelevance Window / decay indicatorStatus badge (Proposed / Under Review / Approved / Rejected / Expired)
Key Interactions:
Filter by status, type, time window
Sort by confidence, risk, freshness
Click to open Insight Detail
4.2 Insight Detail (Explainability View)
Goal: Full transparency into what PIE is claiming and why.
Sections:
Summary headerOpportunity StatementType, status, versionConfidence and risk summary
Evidence BundleSignals (SIG IDs, trust scores, timestamps)Research artifacts (DRE IDs, confidence)Evidence grouping and corroboration
Scoring & BreakdownScoring model versionFeature contributions (breakdown)
Risks & Counter-signalsRisk flagsExplicit counter evidence
Decay & RelevanceRelevance windowDecay rationale
Governance PanelPromotion readinessGGP decision linkage (if applicable)
4.3 Version History (Per Insight)
Goal: Allow auditors and operators to see how an Insight evolved.
Core Elements:
List of versions with:Version numberTimestampReason for change (evidence/model/governance)Key deltas (statement/risk/confidence)
Key Interactions:
Compare versions side-by-side
Pin a version for downstream reference
4.4 Evidence Source Explorer (Optional MVP)
Goal: Inspect signal sources for quality and noise.
Core Elements:
Source health panel (SIG)
Trust score distributions
Noise / decay tracking
This view may be deferred if SIG provides its own visibility.
5. Cross-Engine Visibility Requirements
PIE FE must surface upstream and downstream links:
SIG: show signal IDs and trust scores
DRE: show artifact IDs and confidence annotations
GGP: show governance decision ID and outcome
SIM: show scenario analysis linkage (if available)
PTE: show performance trajectories tied to an approved insight version
PIE FE may link out to these systems, but does not replace them.
6. Component Inventory (Suggested)
